(GROAN5)

06:56.360 --> 06:57.486
Hello?

07:00.560 --> 07:01.971
Oh, good.

07:06.680 --> 07:08.842
What? No, no, no, no. No.

07:08.920 --> 07:10.046
No!

07:15.080 --> 07:17.526
-(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)
-WOMAN: You know that she is sick.

07:18.200 --> 07:19.486
(ARGUING IN DISTINCTLY)

07:23.680 --> 07:24.681
(DOOR OPENING)

07:27.280 --> 07:28.406
Hello?

07:28.520 --> 07:29.851
Good morning, Cosima.

07:31.600 --> 07:32.931
Who are you?

07:33.840 --> 07:35.126
Oh, er...

07:35.560 --> 07:36.721
Right.

07:36.880 --> 07:38.882
Welcome to Revival.

07:39.440 --> 07:41.841
Sustaining life off the grid since 1908.

07:41.920 --> 07:44.810
My name is Mud, and these

07:46.520 --> 07:47.806
are your Wellies.

07:48.720 --> 07:50.370
Do you know where
Delphine wentjust now?

07:51.480 --> 07:53.721
Er... To work, I think, at the clinic.

07:54.520 --> 07:56.682
- She'll be back.
-I really need to talk to her.

07:56.840 --> 07:59.286
I know. It's a lot, right?

07:59.480 --> 08:02.131
You woke up in a yurt. You're wondering
who all these people are.

08:02.200 --> 08:03.964
You just wanna know what's going on.

08:06.200 --> 08:07.531
Yeah, are you gonna tell me?

08:08.160 --> 08:09.161
I'll show you.

08:20.120 --> 08:21.610
This is Revival.

08:27.880 --> 08:29.041
Come on.

08:31.480 --> 08:33.801
MUD: We're almost
completely self-sufficient.

08:33.880 --> 08:36.724
We generate our own power,
we have our own comms.

08:37.200 --> 08:39.441
Great. I...
I need to talk to my sisters.

08:39.520 --> 08:41.886
MUD: Oh, you're not gonna
be allowed to do that.

08:42.400 --> 08:45.529
And our greenhouse is over here.
We raise all our own livestock.

08:45.600 --> 08:47.602
Er, there is a fish farm.

08:47.680 --> 08:49.489
We have everything we need.

08:49.560 --> 08:52.325
All these people are chosen
from every part of the world.

08:52.640 --> 08:55.689
- Why are they here?
-To genetically improve the human race.

08:55.800 --> 08:58.565
We all contribute and we all benefit.

08:59.440 --> 09:02.922
I had some pretty beneficial
science stolen from me.

09:03.160 --> 09:04.969
Do you know Rachel Duncan?

09:07.160 --> 09:08.650
Oh, we do now.

09:09.600 --> 09:11.602
Yeah. This is a big day for all of us.

09:11.680 --> 09:13.762
- She's in seclusion with him.
-With who?

09:14.400 --> 09:15.686
The founder.

09:17.440 --> 09:19.204
We're all his children here.

09:19.680 --> 09:21.648
COSIMA: You lost me.
Who? Whose children?

09:22.120 --> 09:23.804
P .T. Westmorla n d .

09:24.960 --> 09:27.042
He lives here, with us.

09:27.840 --> 09:28.841
COSIMA: Really?

09:29.680 --> 09:31.682
How old is old P.T. now?

09:32.040 --> 09:33.963
One-hundred and seventy, lastjune.

09:34.920 --> 09:36.888
Are you familiar with his 1880 paper

09:36.960 --> 09:39.566
on post-subjectivity
and collective research living?

09:39.640 --> 09:41.290
It's totally visionary.

09:41.800 --> 09:43.370
Wow. Okay.

09:48.280 --> 09:51.090
- Cosima.
-Hey, Charlotte.

09:51.480 --> 09:53.403
Oh, my God. Hey.

09:53.560 --> 09:55.688
Tweedle small and Tweedle tall.

09:55.800 --> 09:56.926
Just ignore her.

09:57.160 --> 10:00.209
- What were you doing in there?
-It's sort of a school.

10:02.120 --> 10:03.804
Okay. That's weird.

10:04.120 --> 10:05.121
Er...

10:05.720 --> 10:07.006
How are you feeling?

10:07.080 --> 10:09.447
I'm feeling okay,
but what happened to your treatment?

10:11.080 --> 10:13.162
You let me worry about that, okay?

10:13.600 --> 10:16.763
Delphine, my friend, she's got our back.

10:17.000 --> 10:19.890
- What about Susan? Is she okay?
-I heard she'll pull through.

10:20.200 --> 10:22.521
- How did you hear that?
-Rumours.

10:22.840 --> 10:24.330
P.T. and Susan go way back,

10:24.400 --> 10:26.402
but family feuds, who's to say?

10:30.560 --> 10:31.686
(DOOR CLOSING)

10:48.960 --> 10:50.246
(SIGHS)

10:52.280 --> 10:53.281
(DOOR OPENS)

10:58.120 --> 10:59.406
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

11:00.400 --> 11:01.526
(DOOR SHUTS)

11:05.680 --> 11:06.681
(SCREAMS)

11:06.760 --> 11:08.489
Oh, God! It's me!

11:08.560 --> 11:10.289
Oh, my God, Arthur!

11:10.720 --> 11:12.165
I almost hit you with a pan!

11:12.240 --> 11:14.163
Yeah, well, I almost shot you,
so we're even.

11:14.640 --> 11:15.641
(SIGHS)

11:17.520 --> 11:18.601
Did you find anything?

11:22.000 --> 11:24.731
Corkscrew through the back
of the hand, pub-fighting.

11:24.800 --> 11:25.847
Classic Siobhan.

11:26.400 --> 11:27.765
That's a good thing.

11:27.840 --> 11:29.524
Now Ferdinand's pissed off.

11:30.320 --> 11:32.049
Er, I just need you to think.

11:32.480 --> 11:33.845
Where would he take them?

11:34.200 --> 11:36.487
I need you to tell me
that we've got something to go on here.

11:36.560 --> 11:38.483
Hey, there's always something to go on.

11:40.400 --> 11:42.528
I can't contact Siobhan's network.

11:43.800 --> 11:46.610
- I'm worried they're playing, too.
-Look, I'm gonna help you.

11:47.160 --> 11:50.369
But there's a Vice on me down at the
station right now over the Duko thing.

11:50.440 --> 11:53.091
I don't even know who's legit
police and who's Neo right now.

11:53.640 --> 11:55.051
- So, one favour.
-Yeah.

11:55.120 --> 11:56.121
The Hendrixs,

11:56.480 --> 11:57.925
make sure they stay put.

11:58.000 --> 11:59.809
We can't put anyone else in harm's way.

11:59.880 --> 12:01.166
Yeah, I'll pass it on.

12:02.560 --> 12:04.369
Kira and Siobhan are gonna be all right.

12:05.240 --> 12:07.049
Okay? We'll find them.

12:09.080 --> 12:10.969
<i>FELIX: Art and me,
we 're hatching a plan, okay?</i>

12:11.040 --> 12:12.371
<i>We're gonna get them
back soon, I promise.</i>

12:12.440 --> 12:13.805
ALISON: Felix, what do you
need us to do?

12:13.880 --> 12:16.690
<i>Nothing. I don't need anything.
just... Where's Helena?</i>

12:16.760 --> 12:18.364
She's out hunting.

12:18.440 --> 12:19.566
Trapping-

12:19.640 --> 12:21.483
It's all categorised as hunting, Donnie.

12:21.560 --> 12:23.722
<i>DONNXE". I know.
But specifically, she's trapping.</i>

12:23.880 --> 12:25.484
Okay, this is dire, Donnie.

12:25.600 --> 12:28.922
He needs some ideas of concrete
plan on how to save Kira.

12:29.160 --> 12:31.731
No, no, no, I don't, Donnie.
I just you to stay put

12:31.800 --> 12:33.723
and stay safe, Art's request.

12:33.960 --> 12:35.086
<i>Just keep yourselves,</i>

12:35.160 --> 12:38.084
<i>and particularly,
Helena the blonde under wraps for now.</i>

12:38.160 --> 12:40.208
He's right. Think of our babies.

12:40.280 --> 12:41.691
<i>FELIX: Great.
I'll talk to you guys soon.</i>

12:42.000 --> 12:43.240
Okay? Bye.

12:43.440 --> 12:45.124
Felix? Oh!

12:45.200 --> 12:47.328
Poop on a stoop,
we don't even know what the plan is.

12:47.400 --> 12:49.050
The plan is to sit tight.

12:50.400 --> 12:52.721
- Sit tight in a national park?
-Yes!

12:52.800 --> 12:55.804
Right, with Sarah stranded
and Kira missing,

12:55.880 --> 12:57.769
and no word from Cosima?

12:58.360 --> 13:01.569
- Yes?
-Well, get packing, mister.

13:09.080 --> 13:10.206
Bell.

13:10.840 --> 13:12.285
I got a present for you.

13:13.120 --> 13:14.406
Yeah, what's that?

13:14.560 --> 13:15.721
Maddie?

13:17.080 --> 13:18.570
You know Maddie Enger?

13:19.200 --> 13:20.645
Hey, Art.

13:20.720 --> 13:22.085
We met before.

13:22.720 --> 13:24.722
Yeah. Vice, right?

13:24.880 --> 13:26.962
- Big time.
-Vice is not her current problem.

13:27.040 --> 13:28.929
Her current problem is
she's a misogynist.

13:29.600 --> 13:32.410
My partner was overly-versed
in sensitivity training.

13:32.480 --> 13:36.087
Regardless, there's a divorce in the
family, so we're shuffling the deck.

13:36.800 --> 13:38.484
You finally got a new partner, Art.

13:38.960 --> 13:40.530
My advice to you both,

13:40.800 --> 13:42.564
go at it slowly this time, huh?

13:42.880 --> 13:43.961
Make it last.

13:45.920 --> 13:47.001
Just like that, huh?

13:47.840 --> 13:49.205
Just like that.

13:50.280 --> 13:51.520
(GRUNTING)

14:21.480 --> 14:22.686
Hold still here.

14:22.760 --> 14:25.001
- No sign of <i>her.</i>
- Where's Ama r?

14:25.480 --> 14:27.801
<i>- Come 'm, Amar.
-I'm just upstream, Cooper.</i>

14:27.880 --> 14:30.042
<i>- I'm bringing the dogs from the village.
- H</i> urry <i>up.</i>

14:30.120 --> 14:31.406
The old man was clear.

14:31.800 --> 14:34.644
We don't go home until she's back
at Revival with the other one.

14:34.720 --> 14:36.051
<i>Rogerthat.</i>

14:38.880 --> 14:40.120
"Revival"?

15:00.560 --> 15:01.561
(GRUNTING)

15:08.960 --> 15:10.325
You're Afghan?

15:11.440 --> 15:12.726
From Afghanistan?

15:13.360 --> 15:16.091
- Yes.
-(SPEAKING PASHTO)

15:18.960 --> 15:20.485
Do you speak English, Aisha?

15:21.000 --> 15:22.570
Do you know why you are here?

15:23.120 --> 15:24.406
To get better.

15:24.680 --> 15:25.681
Yeah.

15:26.480 --> 15:28.084
Can you open your mouth for me?

15:28.640 --> 15:29.801
Thank you.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.480
(SPEAKING PASHTO)

15:34.560 --> 15:36.688
We came for the fountain.

15:44.400 --> 15:45.686
Good luck.

16:08.800 --> 16:09.881
(TH UMPING ON DOOR)

16:09.960 --> 16:11.371
Why is this door locked?

16:11.440 --> 16:12.566
DELPHINE: What?

16:13.360 --> 16:14.361
Open up.

16:15.200 --> 16:16.361
I'm coming.

16:16.600 --> 16:17.886
Open it!

16:23.640 --> 16:27.008
New arrivals just left, they must have
locked it on their way out.

16:30.200 --> 16:32.168
- What?
-It's time.

16:32.920 --> 16:34.331
He wants to see you.

16:35.160 --> 16:36.286
Me?

16:36.600 --> 16:37.601
Why?

16:38.120 --> 16:39.121
Now.

16:47.240 --> 16:49.288
All satellite maps
to the island are blurred,

16:49.360 --> 16:51.681
but Susan's compound is

16:52.920 --> 16:54.888
down here, boathouse,

16:56.200 --> 17:00.410
here, and the village
is up here somewhere.

17:00.480 --> 17:02.562
IRA: They call it "Revival",
but that's all I know.

17:02.720 --> 17:05.848
Susan hasn't been there in years.
She avoided the subject altogether.

17:05.920 --> 17:07.523
You expect us to believe that?

17:07.839 --> 17:10.127
Ira, Rachel has forsaken you,

17:10.200 --> 17:12.964
so for God's sake, pick a bloody side.

17:15.560 --> 17:16.800
Bollocks.

17:17.160 --> 17:19.049
Now would be time
for some good news, Scott.

17:19.359 --> 17:21.681
Sorry, Felix. It's enough to
start a rescue mission, but...

17:21.760 --> 17:25.401
Scott, how?jet skis, frogmen?
I'm on a bicycle, boys.

17:25.480 --> 17:27.403
Well, we're reaching out
to the mast one.

17:27.760 --> 17:29.524
What do you mean? MK?

17:30.640 --> 17:34.008
That's good, actually.
She's skilled, but skittish.

17:34.240 --> 17:36.163
How exactly does one reach out?

17:36.400 --> 17:37.925
Well, we know she games hard, right?

17:38.040 --> 17:41.840
So I spammed hundreds of platforms with
hundreds of avatars named Sarah Manning.

17:41.920 --> 17:43.445
We'll see who gloms.

17:43.520 --> 17:45.045
I've no idea what he just said,

17:45.120 --> 17:47.361
but MK once contacted Kira
through a game.

17:47.440 --> 17:49.169
<i>- It was this, erm...
- Minecraft.</i>

17:49.240 --> 17:51.766
Thank you. I saw her
playing on her laptop at the safe house.

17:51.840 --> 17:53.444
- Do you think that would help?
-It could, yeah.

17:53.520 --> 17:55.409
Great. All right, I'm on it.

17:55.480 --> 17:56.686
Just keep after him.

18:01.400 --> 18:03.368
MADDIE: Major crimes. Man.

18:03.440 --> 18:04.851
I tell ya, it's good to be back home.

18:05.040 --> 18:07.042
ART: Then why are we so far
outside the city limits?

18:10.440 --> 18:13.410
Do you have a case, Maddie,
or a reason why we're out here?

18:13.960 --> 18:15.405
Yeah. I wanna make out.

18:17.480 --> 18:18.481
(GURGLING)

18:21.640 --> 18:23.290
Oh, the file's here somewhere.

18:23.800 --> 18:25.165
- You ever work Vice?
-No.

18:25.240 --> 18:29.131
The things I saw down there, sex stuff,
extreme body-mod torture crap.

18:29.200 --> 18:30.645
That shit'll rot your teeth out.

18:31.480 --> 18:34.609
But this is truly incestuous.

18:43.560 --> 18:44.846
Mmm.

18:44.920 --> 18:46.206
No cracks.

18:46.440 --> 18:47.441
Still.

18:47.920 --> 18:49.649
Damn, you're a survivor.

18:49.720 --> 18:52.803
But the thing is, your preppy friends
are only worth what they know.

18:54.280 --> 18:56.362
And I'm betting
they know where this one is.

18:57.560 --> 18:58.846
You ever meet the psycho?

18:59.120 --> 19:00.565
Running around all pregnant.

19:00.960 --> 19:02.689
No. Never seen her.

19:06.800 --> 19:07.847
I'm realising,

19:08.520 --> 19:11.808
you don't know how far we're willing to
go to bring all these clones in.

19:12.400 --> 19:14.289
You better embrace this new future, Art,

19:14.520 --> 19:16.602
'cause it's gonna be here real soon.

19:27.120 --> 19:28.531
(BLOWING CALL)

19:33.320 --> 19:34.845
(BLOWING CALL)

19:36.600 --> 19:38.648
Yes. Skills!

19:38.720 --> 19:40.324
What the dickens are you doing?

19:40.400 --> 19:42.004
I'm loon-calling Helena.

19:42.440 --> 19:44.727
I'm likejeremiahjohnson over here.

19:44.800 --> 19:47.804
- She's close, by the way.
-Good. Well, I packed all of her things.

19:47.880 --> 19:48.961
Yeah, yeah.

19:49.600 --> 19:50.761
(BRANCHES CREAKING)

